The snack consists of a tortilla that can be filled with any food, then just fold and taste. Such flexibility guarantees a varied menu of options. Guacamole is a typical delicacy of Mexican cuisine, served with a wide variety of dishes and usually accompanied with pico-de-gallo and sour cream. This snack is made from a special corn flour called nixtamal, or nixtamalized corn. Chili con carne is a spicy stew made with meat and beans and is one of the most popular dishes in Mexican cuisine. The chili con carne recipe is simple and practical to prepare and gains a spicy flavor with the use of jalapeño pepper and cayenne pepper. Burrito is a traditional dish of Mexican cuisine, consisting of a flour tortilla usually stuffed with various ingredients, most variants use beans and meat (beef, pork or chicken) with side dishes. Nachos are a popular food in the United States and Mexico. The dish consists of crispy, triangular-shaped corn tortillas topped with cheese and jalapeño pepper.
